HEADWORD: Scherzo
<hw>Scher"zo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A playful, humorous movement, commonly in 3-4
measure, which often takes the place of the old minuet and trio in a
sonata or a symphony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

